        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 4:10PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 410 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles south of Hartwell, or 4 miles east of Bowman, moving southwest
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bowman, Dewy Rose, Nuberg, and Vanna.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
